name: Compass
description: Inktober prompt day 16: Compass made with pen and ink physical drawing using micron pen and background images are random cell phone images from years ago. Ancient times. I wanted to dive into the concept of feeling like we are told what to value/how we interact and didn't want to take this compass prompt too literally. We glorify going north towards something greater, too much focus is placed on defining sex/gender/what we have in our "southern regions", and on either side East and West the messages we say and receive often feel like polar opposites.
